BY HEMBADOON ORSAR MAKURDI Governor Samuel Ortom has said that the death of the Chairman, Buruku Local Government Area, Hon. Daniel Deajir is shocking and devastating. A statement by the Chief Press Secretary Terver Akase described Hon Deajir as a gentleman and diligent administrator who was already making positive impact in his stewardship of the local government before his sudden death. According to him, the demise of the Council Chairman is a blow to the entire state. He however console the government and people of Buruku, particularly the Deajir family over the irreparable loss, while praying for the reposed of his soul. Mean while the Deputy chairman Hon. Andrew Iorver has already been sworn-in to replace late Deajir.